-- Loan disbursements at Brazil's BNDES soar 35 pct in Jan-Feb
-- By Rodrigo Viga Gaier
-- Thu Mar 27, 2014 11:54AM EDT
-- None



RIO DE JANEIRO, March 27 (Reuters) - Loan disbursements at Brazil's state development bank BNDES [BNDES.UL], the largest source of long-term corporate credit in the country, surged 35 percent in the first two months of this year, according to a statement on Thursday.

BNDES lent 28.5 billion reais ($12.6 billion) in January and February, the statement said.